Process called "setup_menu_hierarchy" that takes menu_bar as MacOSMenuBar returns None:
    Note: Set up proper macOS menu hierarchy with standard menus
    Try:
        Note: Create application menu (leftmost menu)
        Let app_menu be create_application_menu with menu_bar as menu_bar
        Call menu_bar.main_menu.items.insert with index as 0 and item as app_menu
        
        Note: Ensure File menu exists and is properly positioned
        Let file_menu be find_or_create_file_menu with menu_bar as menu_bar
        Call ensure_standard_file_menu_items with menu as file_menu
        
        Note: Ensure Edit menu exists with standard items
        Let edit_menu be find_or_create_edit_menu with menu_bar as menu_bar
        Call ensure_standard_edit_menu_items with menu as edit_menu
        
        Note: Add Window menu with standard items
        Let window_menu be create_window_menu with menu_bar as menu_bar
        Call ensure_standard_window_menu_items with menu as window_menu
        
        Note: Add Help menu (rightmost)
        Let help_menu be find_or_create_help_menu with menu_bar as menu_bar
        Call menu_bar.main_menu.items.append with item as help_menu
        
        Note: Set up menu keyboard shortcuts and mnemonics
        Call configure_menu_keyboard_shortcuts with menu_bar as menu_bar
        
        Note: Apply macOS menu conventions
        Call apply_macos_menu_conventions with menu_bar as menu_bar
        
    Catch error as Exception:
        Call log_integration_error with platform as "macos_menu_hierarchy" and error as error

Process called "assign_menu_bar" that takes main_menu as NSMenu returns None:
    Note: Assign menu bar to macOS application using NSApplication
    Try:
