Process called "nsdocktile_set_badge_label" that takes tile as NSDockTile and label as String returns None:
    Note: Set dock tile badge label with validation and formatting
    Try:
        Note: Validate and sanitize badge label
        Let sanitized_label be label
        If string_length with string as label is greater than 10:
            Set sanitized_label to substring with string as label and start as 0 and length as 10
        
        Note: Update tile badge
        Set tile.badge_label to sanitized_label
        
        Note: Use osascript to update actual dock tile if possible
        Let applescript_cmd be "osascript -e 'tell application \"" plus get_current_app_name plus "\" to set badge of dock tile to \"" plus sanitized_label plus "\"'"
        Let script_result be execute_system_command with command as applescript_cmd
        
        Note: Log badge update for debugging
        If sanitized_label is not equal to "":
            Call log_dock_operation with operation as "set_badge" and details as sanitized_label
    
    Catch error as Exception:
        Call log_dock_error with operation as "set_badge_label" and error as error

